rComments: You can tell he'd be a decent prof in person but online it was incredibly disengaging. The PowerPoints were unnecessarily long and disorganized, I essentially taught myself the entire class. Tests weren't awful but they were all QCM.
Wish I could say something better but this class was done online asynchronously and we were only taught thru powerpoints, no live classes.

I thought I had failed the first midterm and I considered dropping this class, but thankfully the profs boosted the grade. I took this as an elective and I was really looking forward to the class, but I was very disappointed. There was 2 midterms and a final which were very difficult. There was also so much reading and info in the powerpoints.

Wish I could say something better but this class was done online asynchronously and we were only taught thru powerpoints, no live classes. The PWPs were unstimulating and he is very accommodating and sweet but the way the class itself was taught was extremely difficult, I took this as an elective for immersion and regretted it lol. Exams are all MC
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Absolutely amazing prof. Really passionate, and very knowledgable. Thank you very much for the great semester.

Prof Cauchie is great! Very knowledgeable, and his lectures are interesting! All of the important material is in his slides and he tells you exactly what to study for exams! He spoke very fast & with a thick accent, but his detailed slides helped! Overall a great prof, would take another class with him!

Amazing prof! He really cares about students and wants them to succeed. Tells you what the short answer questions on the midterms/exams are and the topics to study for the MC questions. He does speak fast for a French as a second language student but his powerpoints are detailed and if you record him and re-listen later then it's not bad.

Spoke really fast so was tough for a French as a second language student. But, he just read off of powerpoints which he posts online beforehand. Tells you almost exactly what's on midterm and exam in class so it's helpful to go. Tests are only 10 MC and 3 short answer and take 30 minutes to do.

Professeur Cauchie est excellent! Il explique clairement ses attentes et la matière nécessaire aux examens. Il est aussi très sympathique et accessible pour ses étudiants. Si tu écoutes pendant son cours, tu vas surement passer! Pose-lui des questions parce que des fois son vocabulaire riche et son accent sont difficiles à comprendre.

Un cours très facile. Toutes les lectures à faire sont en ligne et il y a aucun manuel à acheter. Le professeur donne les questions à « développement » en avance et les réponses doivent être très courtes. Il n'est vraiment pas nécessaire d'aller en classe si tu étudies un peu avant les tests
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures ', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: This professor was very entertaining and always pointed out what we should study. Very interesting class and very interesting prof.

Funny and caring teacher, simple exams and easy grader. If you don't come to class you won't be penalized in any way. He pinpoints the exact questions on the exam and puts a document online so everyone can prepare and get an easy A. I definitely recommend this teacher.

Really caring prof, he wants to see his students excel. He will be very clear on exam content, just make sure to show up to class to hear these explanations. He has a europeen accent and talks very fast so that was the challenging aspect of this prof. All in all though, he is a great prof and person!

As a French Immersion student, I will say that he is a little difficult to understand, but his lectures are very clear so you can do well that way. He wants all his students to do well and I would take his class again.
Awsome!

Amazing Prof! Would definitely take again if I could. He teaches first year and fourth year and will make sure all of his students pass. Honestly, if you get anything less than an A- it's probably because you didn't try at all.

Il est cool, il fait beaucoup de blague. Je les trouvais douteuses mais bon, les Européens ! C'est un gars très cool qui ne se prend pas trop au sérieux, dans son cours seulement deux travaux, 40% et 60%. Il corrige vite ! Il donnait l'option de donner le travail en papier ou courriel, mais corrige le papier et donne la donne avant -_-
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: C'est un excellent professeur. Allez au cours et vous saurez ce qui est le plus important à l'examen. A+ facile si vous l'écoutez bien. Les examens sont parfaitement représentatifs de la matière.
Cours super intéressant. Le prof est vraiment sympathique, comique et inspirant.

Excellent professeur et d'ailleurs le meilleur que j'ai eu durant mon parcours à l'université! Connaît très bien sa matière et l'enseigne bien. Si vous allez à tous ces cours et vous écoutez quand il mentionne ce qu'on doit étudier pour les examens facile de réussir!

Really easy to get A+. He literally tells you what is important to study, what will be a multiple choice question or development. For each theme, you have some reading and he goes over them in class. If you did your readings and answered the questions that go with them, with only two or one days of studying you can get an A+. Great teacher!

This professor is smart and clever. He is one of the best professor I ever had before. He has a great European accent and sense of humor. He knows what he is talking about and he is empathic and resilient. I really enjoyed his classes. This professor has ability to teach not only 1st year class, but even teach other professors. I recommend JF.C
Il est vraiment un bon professeur. Il mentionne toujours ce qui est nécessaire sur l'examen et le repete toujours a plusieurs cours.

I highly recommend this class! Best prof I ever had at UOttawa. He gives you exactly whats on all 3 exams and is there after class if you have any questions or comments about the class. His so funny and his lectures are really interesting!

DONC, such an amazing human. He's an all-around scholar. He knows his material. He's honest. He's caring. He makes you feel good even if you get a bad grade and he wants to talk to his students. Tells you what's on the exam and clarifies questions during the exam. He is hilarious and really good for anglophones. What a God. Oui...

Very good professor, clear on what is going to be evaluated; however, the majority of his exams are multiple choice (a-f) and the correct answer is rarely evident. Material is not cumulative which is a bonus. Overall, very good professor.

Comprend combien la vie étudiante peut être occupée. Ses examens furent les plus claires et justes que j'aie jamais eu à subir. J'ai assistée à toutes les cours et faite les qque lectures ainsi qu'1-2 heures d'étude avant chaque examen et c'était amplement suffisant. Ses magistrales sont engageantes, il est passionné, je le recommande fortement

Meilleur professeur au monde. Il a la réussite de ses étudiants à cœur Il est toujours disponible en dehors des heures de cours pour expliquer la matière. Si on manque un cours il est prêt à l'expliquer par courriel. Très compréhensif sur tous les points.

His exams are short (half multiple choice, half short answer questions) and non-cumulative and he tells you what's on them. The multiple choice can leave you second guessing your answers, but he does his best to help. He tells you exactly what you need to know if you see him at his office hours before the exams! great prof!

The best prof I've ever had. One midterm and two projects. Midterm was extremely short for a 4th year class (3 questions, 10-15 lines), but the projects were long and heavy (I suggest starting them in advance and having a team). Either way, the prof is ALWAYS available when needed and goes above and beyond with the feedback. He's more than fair.

He's a great prof, but he's sly. There are only three exams but they are created in such a way where you second guess yourself and change answers constantly. His lectures are relatively engaging and he can be easily access after class.
If you go to class you will do well

Great prof, he is very clear with what he wants as an answer and even gives ALL of the midterm/exam questions before hand (even multiple choice questions for final exam). He posts all of his power points online and they have most of the information needed. He does have a thick accent and can be hard to understand at times.
Great prof! Can explain very well and make you understand everything you need to know. BEWARE OF HIS EXAMS!! Very very tricky and can make you lose points even tho you knew the answer!

An amazing prof however he speaks so fast. If you're not french as a first language it's super hard to understand and pay attention to what he's talking about. Posts everything online so it's very easy to study, just make sure you go to lectures and pay attention!

Très bon professeur. Les cours et lectures sont intéressants. Les examens peuvent paraître compliqués, mais le professeur explique pendant les cours ce qu'il attend exactement de nous. Une bonne écoute en cours permet donc de facilement réussir cette classe.
Not a bad guy at all. Hes pretty funny and his lectures are pretty good. But he is a tough grader though so definitively don't expect a relatively easy pass.
Excellent professeur. Très difficile de couler ses examens considérant qu'il mentionne mots pour mots ce qui est important à retenir (il le répète plusieurs fois d'ailleurs).
One of the most caring prof! Definitely recommend him!

Ce professeur est super gentil, drôle, accessible pour les étudiants. Il est toujours prêt à répéter et ré-expliquer pendant ses office hours aux personnes qui ont plus de difficultés. Ses examens sont SUPER prévisible. Pendant les cours, il dit quelles notions sont importantes et quelles questions seront à l'examen. Super bon prof!

Prof cares about students and the lectures are well explained but their's a lot of content... make sure you take time to read the slides after class. Not doing the readings and skiping class will get you a bad mark.
Best prof ever

This teacher is awesome! His tests are super easy if you make a minimum of effort. He puts all the readings online so you don't even have to buy a textbook! He tells you what you need to get out of the readings and basically what's going to be on the test. If you need extra help or have a question - he answers emails right away!

Excellent professeur. Le langage dans ses notes de cours est un peu difficile à comprendre mais c'est le seul point négatif sur lui. Il dit à l'avance exactement ce qu'il y aura à l'examen. Si vous écoutez durant les cours ce qui dit qu'il est important, vous aurez de bonnes notes c'est assuré!

Super professeur. Très gentil et abordable. Il est tough en notation mais il donne du très bon feedback. Il rend son cours très intéressant et fait toujours des blagues. C'est un excellent professeur, un des meilleurs que j'ai eu à date !!

EXCELLENT professeur. Il explique  classe clairement ce qui va être à l'examen. Cours très intéressant et facile. Présentez-vous en classe et vous obtiendrez les questions et les réponses aux examens :)
He is one of my best professor.
always helpful and available for further clarification. Made it crystal clear as to what would be on the exams...

Very nice, clear and helpful. Gives great advice and as long as you've made sure you clearly understood everything, it's easy to achieve perfect marks. Readings help to understand better, but you can easily have A's without them. Overall the midterms and the final are very easy (if you understand his way of doing them). I loved this class!
Très bon prof! Très gentil et près à aider.

This prof is really knowledgeable and is always willing to help his students. The class is interesting and pretty easy if you read the texts, although his midterms can be tricky when it comes to the multiple choice questions. Overall I would recommend him, hes nice to look at too...

J'ai eu ce prof pour plusieurs cours et je dois dire qu'il est très sympathique envers ses étudiants et veut voir leur réussite. Très approchable et serviable. Un prof qui, visiblement, adore ce qu'il fait et sait semer la passion pour la criminologie chez ses étudiants!
Kinda hard to understand and likes to veer off subject from time to time. Overall, the class is interesting enough, but i would rather have a different prof.

J'ai été un peu déçu. C'est vrai qu'il est un bon prof, mais ça ne rend pas ses examens plus faciles pour autant. Personnellement, je trouve que pour un cours d'introduction à la crimino, son contenu aurait pu être mieux. D'autant plus que le recueil DOIT être lu pour réussir le cours. Finalement, je trouvais qu'il était parfois long et plate...
très bon professeur!! un des meilleurs que j'ai eu jusqu?à maintenant à l'université
Bon prof! Un des meilleurs. Ces exams sont faciles si tu comprend bien la matière. Il a un accent mais il s'explique très bien. Je le recommande à tous! Garde: Lisez vos recueils!
Awesome teacher!! Probably one of the reasons i love crimilogy so much! Not bad on the eyes too ;)
Très bon professeur
Not much to say beside...BEST teacher I ever had!
très bon professeur!
Bonjour, à vos souhaits. :)
AWESOME Prom. I absolutely loved him. He made everything interesting. Exams are hard, alot of memorizing. But he's all and all a great great teacher.

i had the pleasure of having him for both CRM 1700 & 1701. If you attend class you berly have to read the texts and you can get an A. He is super helpful, let me come see him with questions 1 hour before the exam & offered to meet with me (which lasted over 1 hour) to give me info on Belgium (i'm doing a student exchange there) best teacher ever
Interesting prof, but his accent is kinda hard to listen to, and his exams dont really reflect the class material

He's very helpful and the course is very easy as long as you do the readings.  Sometimes the slides can be very hard to understand.  He's very approachable and wants his students to succeed.  It's not too hard to get an A or A+ in his class if you put some effort into it.  Plus, you get to look at him all semester.

Le cours semble tout d'abord un peu lourd, les diapos sont dans les mots du prof et c'est dur de saisir l'essentiel, mais si on relit les diapos et les texte avant l'examen, le prof est tres genereux dans sa correction alors c'est facile de s'en sortir avec une tres bonne note.
Excellent teacher! Explains really well, and it helps that he's easy on the eye ;)
Complicated for nothing goes around the same thing over and over and still not any clearer.  You have to think the same way he does or else youll do bad in the class

If you go to class and do the readings, you're good to go. Very interesting course content and great sense of humour. Very helpful if you have any questions. He wants to see his students succeed. Not in Crim, but loved this prof!

Meilleur Prof a date! Il est résonable, claire et se met dans les souliers des étudiants. Il te pousse a réfléchir et veut toujours aider meme si sa veut dire rester 45 min apres le cours pour donner des explication supplémentaire! Ses examens n'ont aucuns pieges. Si tu te présente au cours il y a aucune raison pour ne pas réussir.
He makes the course. Explains very well and is very interesting and funny.
xxx
Excellent prof!
Good teacher.... fun to look at!

Un excellent prof, extremement compétent surtout pour un nouveau prof! Enfin, un chercheur avec de la pédagogie ! Je le classe au même niveau que Beauchesne, Acosta (coté du savoir) etc... et en plus il est mignon!!!
Great prof! One of the better profs I have ever had. Maybe the best! And he is SOOOO HOOOOOO!! and his Belgium accent is just irresistible!
Excellent professeur!
Teacher is very helpful, always ready to help and very interesting.  And must say.. he is really hot!!
His Belgium accent is sexy.
georgeous is the perfect word to describe him!! WOW..
georgeous!!!!!!!!!!
He is really there to help you but so much complicated for nothing
